Feature: the canonical BC CLAUDE.md primer pins end-of-turn continuation so a BC drains the next inbox item after a work_done emit without checking in

  lead-hdn3 (P1) — BC-side analogue of the lead primer's "Standing rule: end-of-turn
  continuation" (lead-primer.md §37). Observed 2026-06-01 on bc-shopsystem-templates:
  the BC consumed lead-8hxz cleanly (implementer → reviewer → work_done emit), then on
  the next inbox check PAUSED and asked its session-lead "which message would you like
  me to dispatch first, or shall I take them in order?" — the prodding pattern. The
  canonical BC primer must pin between-item autonomous continuation: completing one item
  is not a stopping point; it is the trigger to start the next ready inbox item. This is
  package-data primer prose, not a per-shop hand-edit.

  PRE-AUTHORED — dispatch deferred (BC-reliability serialization behind stranded
